<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 93-16-01 - Process to Remove Medium to Heavy Oxidation From Cab and Hood Painted Surfaces</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi931601" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>93-16-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>February, 1993</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Process to Remove Medium to Heavy Oxidation From Cab and Hood Painted Surfaces</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Older vehicles that were painted with earlier paint technologies such as lacquers, enamels, and
                    acrylics are all vulnerable to color oxidation. When these vehicles are waxed, it is this oxidation
                    that appears as "color" on the polish cloth.
                </para>
                <para>With the introduction of Urethane Base Coat/Clear Coat on all Navistar vehicles, oxidation is no
                    longer an issue.
                </para>
                <para>Navistar has tested and approved the following process for owners of older vehicles who wish to
                    extend the time between waxing, while maintaining the shiny appearance of their vehicle for a longer
                    period of time.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>PROCESS TO REMOVE MEDIUM TO HEAVY OXIDATION</title>
            <para>See
                <hotlnk xrefid="t9316011">Table 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <table id="t9316011" frame="all">
                <title>Process to Remove Medium to Heavy Oxidation</title>
                <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.72in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="4.78in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col2" spanname="1to2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP ONE - WASHING</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry morerows="1" valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Products:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #62 Carwash and Conditioner (M6201)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry valign="top"></entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP ONE - WASHING (Cont.)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Process:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Follow Meguiar's instructions to wash all painted surfaces.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP TWO - BUFFING</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Products:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #15 Clear Coat Conditioner</para>
                                <para>Meguiar's W-7000 Cutting Pad</para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #2 Hi-Tech Cleaner (if necessary)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP TWO - BUFFING (Cont.)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Process:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Apply Meguiar's #15 Clear Coat Conditioner to the area to be buffed, and smear
                                    material evenly with pad before starting buffer. Start the buffer
                                    <emph type="bold">(recommended RPM 1750 to 2000)</emph>
                                    and keep the buffer pad flat on the painted surface using medium to light pressure.
                                    To avoid heat build-up, do not buff the conditioner after it starts to dry. DRY
                                    BUFFING COULD
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>D DAMAGE PAINT. Wipe clean with a soft cloth.
                                </para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>NOTE: If oxidation is still noticeable, use Meguiar's #2 Hi-Tech Cleaner and
                                        repeat the process.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP THREE - POLISHING</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Products:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #15 Clear Coat Conditioner</para>
                                <para>Meguiar's W-9000 Finish Pad</para>
                                <para>Meguiar's W-6000 D.A. Polish Pad</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP THREE - POLISHING (Cont.)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Process:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Apply Meguiar's #15 Clear Coat conditioner to area to be polished, and smear
                                    material evenly with a W-9000 finish pad before starting buffer. Polish by keeping
                                    the pad flat against the surface using medium to light pressure (
                                    <emph type="bold">recommended RPM 1750 to 2000</emph>).
                                </para>
                                <para>To avoid heat build-up, do not buff the conditioner after it starts to dry.
                                    <emph type="bold">DRY BUFFING COULD DAMAGE PAINT</emph>.
                                </para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>If swirls are visible, use a D.A. random orbital adapted with Meguiar's W-6000
                                        D.A. Polishing Pad and Meguiar's #15 Clear Coat Conditioner.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP FOUR - PROTECT</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Product:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #26 Hi-Tech Yellow Wax (Liquid or Paste)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP FOUR - PROTECT (Cont.)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Process:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Can be applied by hand or machine. Follow recommended instructions.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP FIVE - MAINTAIN</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Products:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Meguiar's #34 Final Inspection</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP FIVE - MAINTAIN (Cont.)</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Process:</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Follow recommended instructions.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2" valign="top">
                                <note>
                                    <para>Meguiar products can be obtained locally where you purchase your parts or
                                        paint supplies.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
